OL,7,FThe headline-grabbing elements of the
OL,8,Fgovernment's new law to crack down on
OL,9,Fstreet harassment are that it will ban
OL,10,Fwolf-whistling or catcalling.
OL,12,FBut the kinds of behaviours referenced
OL,13,Fin the consultation ranged far beyond
OL,14,Fthis. They include suggestive language,
OL,15,Fgestures or propositioning; following a
OL,16,Fvictim or slowing to block their path;
OL,17,Fand staring or leering.
OL,19,FThe decision to come forward with this
OL,20,Flaw is, as the Home Secretary herself
OL,21,Fsaid, a "complex" one.
OL,3,CA crackdown on wolf-whistling and worse
OL,4,Cstreet harassment is vital if it can be
OL,5,Cenforce
